# Development

## Prerequisites

Install [Hatch](https://hatch.pypa.io/latest/install/):

```bash
pip install hatch
```

## Setting Up

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/{{ github_username }}/{{ project_name }}.git
cd {{ project_name }}
```

## Running the Example Project

The repo includes an `example_project` so you can test `{{ module_name }}` immediately:

```bash
hatch run project:migrate
hatch run project:createsuperuser
hatch run project:runserver
```

Then open [http://127.0.0.1:8000](http://127.0.0.1:8000).

## Running Tests

Run tests across all supported Python + Django version combinations:

```bash
hatch run test:test
```

Run tests for a specific combination (e.g. Python 3.12 + Django 5.0):

```bash
hatch run test.py3.12-5.0:test
```

See all available environments:

```bash
hatch env show
```

## Coverage

```bash
hatch run test:cov
```

This prints a coverage summary and writes a JSON report used by the CI upload to Codecov.

## Pre-commit Hooks

Install the pre-commit hooks:

```bash
pip install pre-commit
pre-commit install
```

Hooks run automatically on commit. To run them manually against all files:

```bash
pre-commit run --all-files
```

## Code Style

- **Black** — code formatting
- **Ruff** — linting and import sorting
- **codespell** — spell checking
- **pyupgrade** — upgrades Python syntax to newer versions

All of these run as pre-commit hooks. You can also run Ruff directly:

```bash
hatch run ruff check .
hatch run ruff format .
```

## CI

Every push and pull request to `main` runs the CI workflow, which tests against:

- **Python**: 3.10, 3.11, 3.12, 3.13, 3.14
- **Django**: 5.0, 5.1, 5.2, 6.0

Coverage results are uploaded to Codecov automatically.

